    "narrative": "The Austin Waves roster is positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Josh Lowe** (70.92) and **Gunnar Henderson** (67.58), our strongest starts against favorable matchups. **Josh Lowe** benefits from a distinct combination of a soft matchup against Davis Martin and a wind-assisted environment, with his dynamic platoon advantage providing the necessary upside to anchor the outfield. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** remains an elite play despite facing Cam Schlittler; his high score is bolstered by a 14% platoon boost and his prime position in the order. In the outfield, **Heliot Ramos** (64.53) also earns a premium start, as he faces Randy V\u00e1squez in a matchup where his 19% SP skill advantage outweighs his slight park-factor drag.\n\nWhile the core is set, we have carefully navigated a few marginal decisions in the lower tiers. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.07) maintains his utility spot despite a park-factor penalty, thanks to a strong matchup against Nick Martinez and elevated xwOBA metrics. Conversely, **Coby Mayo** (40.71) serves as our most notable bench decision; he narrowly missed the starting cut due to a negative platoon split against Cam Schlittler and lower priority in the lineup hierarchy compared to **Miguel Vargas** (49.80). We are also monitoring the status of **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks** closely, as their scores are currently tethered to projected spots in the batting order; should official lineups reveal them dropping down the order, their efficiency scores\u2014already hovering near the marginal threshold\u2014will likely fall, potentially forcing a defensive re-evaluation. \n\nOur primary risk factor today remains the \"Lineup Pending\" status for nearly every position, which introduces variance in our order-dependent bonuses. We are effectively betting on **Sam Antonacci** (#1) and **Heliot Ramos** (#1) to capitalize on their high-volume spots to drive our stolen base floor, a critical necessity given the scarcity of the category. With **Luis Robert Jr.** remaining sidelined on the IL, the onus is on the active bats to maintain our 5x5 pace. Please note that **Andy Pages** (49.44) is active, but his score is heavily influenced by a narrow margin; keep an eye on his status as his efficiency is tied to a specific SB-favorable interaction with the opposing battery.",
